newsitem.title: JAPAN: Tokyo corn futures end mostly higher.
newsitem.headline: Tokyo corn futures end mostly higher.

text.p: Tokyo corn futures ended mostly higher on Wednesday, as technical buying from individual investors supported the market, traders said.
The benchmark November contract was down 10 yen at 14,430 yen per tonne, and other months were 30 to 250 yen higher. Daily volume was 41,971 lots.

The market had a bearish mood in the early morning, due to the yen's strength against the dollar, the traders said. But technical buying from local investors emerged later, supporting the market, they said.
The spot December contract on the CBOT Project A trading system was being traded at $2.80-1/2 per bushel at 0800 GMT, against $2.79-1/2 at Tuesday's close.
The spot November CBOT soybean futures contract was at $6.93 at 0800 GMT, up from $6.89 at the Tuesday close.
